inn1.comm: and deservedly so. Miles away from the right-hander who swung his hands and missed it comfortably. A loose start by all involved
that too's a little too wide, and left alone
straighter and worked to Bopara at short midwicket
outside off and the first signs of a pitch lacking in pace. Lacking in bounce. That barely carried through to the keeper
bosh! Onto the front foot and flayed over cover-point. Third man didn't have a hope of stopping it to his right
better length and defended on the back foot. Paine wants a single and he's not stopping! Watson is adamant, however, and sends the young buck scurrying back in his box
well timed off the back foot to backward point
starts a little bit too wide of Paine
a leg-cutter is left alone. Good length from Broad, but too wide
now that's much better. Attacking the off stump and it keeps a little low on Paine, whose name is rife for punning later on, but it's well defended on the back foot
an extravagant leave wide of the off stump. No need to touch those just yet
defended on the back foot, and he's a little late on it. Broad's working is way up to 90mph here
again late on it and cuts, but gets a thick inside edge
beaten by a beauty which left him off a length. Superb delivery. A fuller length is the length to bowl on this pitch
bottom edge! But too wide and it doesn't carry to Prior. Only your commentator gets even remotely excited
bang! He's hammered that cut but Rashid scoots round from third man and after a bit of a juggle with his feet, retains his balance and cuts off four. And sends in a very good throw, too
inside edge again
my word, he's absolutely smashed that into Anderson's body. A firm off-drive of ugly power; he got a hand on it did Anderson but it still sped for four. Sheesh. He does nail it, Watson
terrible run! Dabbed to backward point and Watson calls him through, but Collingwood's quick onto it and has all three pegs to aim at, running out Paine by at least two yards!
angling back into Watson who's defending
nudged to leg
brilliant hands from Watson, opening the face quite superbly and running it past slip for four. Class
excellent comeback from Broad, dropping it just slightly shorter
on the back foot, he defends
flicked off his hip behind square. "Easy single to Shah," spits my colleague, Gnasher, the former Lancashire fan
the firmest of drives! His timing is breathtaking when he gets it right. That shot like a bullet to long-on
driven out to long-off, this time
left alone outside off
wide of the crease and this shapes back with the angle, beating White comfortably
straight enough for a nudge to mid-on, and White's off the mark
dabbed out to the off side and they get a quick single
opens the face while driving powerfully. Sidebottom cleans up at third man
not a hope. Beaten all ends up by one which held its own
left alone this time outside off
comes forward and drives defensively to mid-off
on the front foot and he defends very solidly
very straight - White's a little late on it on the front foot, but it's defended solidly nevertheless
angling in on the off stump, and he defends
plays and misses to one which scoots low outside off
fine stroke, cover-driving on the up but only for a single
tries to work this fine but gets a bit of a leading edge, and it finds mid-on
very good line just outside off, and defended off the back foot. White roars "no", as if to remind Watson how to call
elegant flourish of the blade finds him four through extra cover. The placement was the key to that; really neatly played
short of a length and he mistimes a pull. Watson roars his unabashed disgust at not making the most of such a rank long-hop
quicker bouncer at 91mph, but wide of the off stump
another sharp bouncer, again evaded with a sway
another short one is pulled through midwicket
slower and straighter delivery stroked out to the off side
swinging back into him but he opens up into a powerful drive to long-off
wide. Way, way too wide and clumped hard into the ground square of the wicket, and it races away for four. Nothing more than a push from Watson
fuller, straight delivery from Sidebottom forces Watson to defend
that's also a very good line on the off stump, and Watson is cautiously defending
nudged to leg
timed out to the off side
full and just outside the off stump, driven to mid-off and Shah tackles it as though the ball was called Joe Denly
off the back foot, and he got a slight inside edge to leg
slapped off the back foot - that's really well timed for four!
onto the front foot and defends out to cover
a good line just outside off, but White can't make anything of it, dabbing it behind square
shapes back into the right-hander who drives cautiously back to Broad
that spat up at him off a good length, nasty ball but he dealt with it well, playing with soft hands down to third man
too much width from Sidebottom, cut away hard through the covers and this outfield is lightening quick
better line, on middle and off, White comes forward and defends into the covers
flicked nicely off leg stump and with great timing, beats the man at short midwicket and has enough pace to beat deep square-leg as well...not the best of starts for Sidebottom
responds with a bouncer, was quite short and after some thought Nigel Llong decides it was too wide, much to Sidebottom's displeasure
another wide, this time down the leg side and it's an easy decision to call this one
that's where Sidebottom needs to be, on off stump and White pushed back down the pitch
defended into the leg side, no sign of any swing for Sidebottom so he has to concentrate on a tight line and length
worked into the leg side to end the over, Sidebottom tightened up after a wayward start but it still cost 10
short and pulled away fine, it dribbles into the rope as Shah opts not to get the dive out at fine leg...he's not the most athletic and that was a fairly feeble effort
another boundary, and much more power in this one as he pulls sweetly square and no one had a chance of getting close to that
width outside off, but Watson picks out Collingwood at backward point with his cut
opens the face and guides down to third man
defended into the covers
full on the stumps, squeezed down the ground just past the stumps and there's an easy single as mid-on comes round to field
drives and gets a thick outside edge along the ground towards backward point where Collingwood makes an excellent save
plays that open-face shot to third man again, plenty of space with no slips in
defended down to mid off, Sidebottom more consistent so far in this over
on middle, defended comfortably into the leg side
tries to turn this round the corner but takes the pad towards square leg
plays this well into the leg side, was a touch more bounce but he rolled his wrists and keeps the strike
starts with a short ball but gets away with it as Bopara produces an excellent piece of fielding at deep square-leg. He collected, rolled and released the ball almost in one motion
fuller this time, turned into the leg side
angling into the pads again but White can't beat the man at midwicket...84mph from Wright
fuller on middle, White tries to work it away but ends up playing it back towards the bowler
top shot, long half volley and White unfurls a perfect straight drive that rockets past Wright and races away
too short this time, poor stuff really, and White dispatches him through midwicket with really power
horrible ball down the leg side, this is pretty average stuff from England in the last few overs
uses the angle and plays this down to third man
played square on the off side, was trying to find third man but couldn't get it fine enough
pushed up to mid-on, momentarily the thought of a single but that was quickly ditched

nearly for England...White tries to launch this through midwicket, was the slower ball, but it skews off a think inside half of the bat and flies in the air past mid-on as Sidebottom holds his head in his hands
worked off the stumps into the gap at midwicket
driven through the covers out to the deep sweeper
good started, on middle and Watson defends coming forward
nicely flighted, pushed out to midwicket
drags this down, a real long hop, but Watson slams it straight out to deep midwicket...he could have hit that anywhere he wanted
worked into the leg side, doesn't beat midwicket
driven down to long off
nicely bowled to finish, slightly quicker on off stump and Watson punches off the back foot back to the bowler
punched down to long off, looked like a cutter to start with
yep, he's in cutter mode, and Watson flicks into the leg side
holds in the pitch a fraction as Watson punches down to long on
pushed out square on the off side, they set off quickly thinking two is an option but deep cover cuts it off
gentle worked down the ground to long-off...it's fairly quiet at the moment
forced off the back foot to cover who makes a good save...tidy start from Collingwood
tossed up on middle, driven down the pitch and Rashid parries it away to long on as he tries to dive for the save
opens his shoulders with a powerful cover drive, he threw the kitchen sink at that but deep cover managed to cut it off
good stuff from Rashid, nice line on middle and White defends slightly awkwardly into the covers
gets his left leg out of the way and drives down to long off
that looked like a googly, driven firmly down the ground to tick the scoreboard over
another flaying drive, but just brings a single down to long off
worked up to long on
keeps a fraction low as Collingwood cuts his fingers across the ball, jabbed into the leg side
punched into the pitch, bounces over Collingwood's attempted grab and down to long on
worked into the leg side, can't find the gap
gone! There's the breakthrough for England, Watson gets a leading edge back to Collingwood as he tries to work through the leg side and it's a dolly of a catch. Clever bowling from Collingwood
very full and driven back to Collingwood in his follow through
tossed up on middle and White, now wearing a cap, works to midwicket. Pretty rare to see a batsman in a cap...good job Shaun Udal wasn't wearing one yesterday
full toss slammed down to long off, White will feel he missed out a bit on that one
leans forward and defends to the leg side
uses his quick footwork and flicks to midwicket
punched back to the bowler to deflects it out to cover
good finish, Clarke wants to attack but has to defend with bat and pad together
full, swinging and cracked to cover
a nice little dobber just outside off which is dabbed behind square
that's a superb shot. It's a filthy long-hop, mind, but he fairly smashed it off the back foot - standing tall, placing it beautifully
better. Straighter delivery, defended
a squidgy prod through mid-on for a single
pushed back to the bowler
another full toss bashed back to Rashid who can't collect it cleanly
flighted wider of the batsman who squeezes it out to the off side. A little dab, and they steal a single
touch too full to trouble White who deadens the spin on the front foot, stroking out to long-off
down the leg side and nudged to leg

comes down the pitch and drives hard to Rashid's right who dives well and prevents four. The crowd briefly wake up from their depressed slumber at the prospect of six more of these ridiculous ODIs, but it wasn't a catch
well flighted and driven back to the bowler
worked to leg. On one leg. A flamingo flick
very well bowled, tossed up fuller. Just a hint of swing
extremely straight on middle-and-off and he drives it back to the bowler
neat flick through midwicket for two.  Wright's moving quickly on the boundary and sends in a good throw, but they nevertheless jog a single without great need to sprint
driven back to the bowler. Good, straight line of attack
turned to leg
nicely bowled. Standard leggie, tossed up on middle
tossed up outside off, he skips down the pitch and strokes it out to Swann at long-off, who's not yet had a bowl
good length, if just a tiny bit too full. Stroked comfortably back to the bowler
too short this time
that's the length. He's not sure whether to go forward or back, and in the end pats it off the back foot
and that is exactly the right length. Good revs has this ball spinning away from White, dancing down the pitch, and he's beaten in the air. It's miscued short of long-off
flicked to leg

short, faster delivery whipped down to fine leg and they come back for two. Swann sends in a very good and fast throw as White comes back for a dangerous second, and he's well short as Prior smashes down the stumps! Terrific fielding from Swann; poor running and calling from Australia
tossed up on middle. Ferguson nudges
whipped to leg
nudged to leg
defended to leg
well flighted and flicked to leg
nice bit of drift back into Clarke there. Faster from Rashid
driven out to the off side
huge shout from Prior as he's rapped high on the pads, attempting to turn it to leg, and that's not a bad shout at all. But it's going over. Well bowled - good, ripping turn
another leg-stump delivery turning back on Ferguson who whips it to short fine-leg
tossed up high and driven out to long-off
fuller delivery and worked to Broad at mid-on who wings in a throw. But Ferguson's like a whippet on speed
dabbed out to the off side. Top dabbing
good line just outside off. Defends out to the off side
too straight and easily worked through midwicket for a single
driven back hard to the bowler
too short this time, whipped around the corner, but he can only manage a single
nicely flighted just outside off. He comes skipping down the pitch and times it neatly to mid-off
driven hard to mid-on. Faster, flatter ball from Rashid
well bowled. That's gutsy from Rashid, holding back his pace nicely and giving it a fair old rip. defended
some shot! A touch flatter, faster and wider, driven with elegant precision straight to cover
down the pitch and he's nearly done him in the flight, here, but Clarke's got such quick hands that he jabs down on it to get a single to midwicket
beautiful hands here, just dabbing it almost out of Prior's gloves down to third man
a rank long-hop but he gets away with severe punishment. Nudged to long-on
faster ball outside off and he skips down the wicket, punching him hard to long-off
defended out to the off side. No spin or rip from Swann, just yet
steps outside off and bunts him off the back foot to long-on
much faster. Almost Collingwoodish speed and turned to the man himself behind square
driven back to Swann
fuller ball on middle, turned to Collingwood at midwicket who's predictably quick, and shies at the non-striker's stumps but it's wide
a touch shorter - fair bit of turn for Rashid here, too, and Clarke can't make anything of it
gives this excellent flight, luring him into a drive, and he smashes him straight to mid-off before shaking his head in frustration
this is fantastic bowling. Another delivery on middle-and-leg, Clarke's back and back-cuts to short third man
good length, good turn, Clarke's forward and can only defend

shorter and he cuts to get a thick outside edge down to third man. Well, that's a bit of luck for Clarke, but Rashid's had the better of him all over. He's bowled beautifully all day has the young man
straighter ball beats Ferguson outside off
worked out to midwicket
goes back in his crease and whips neatly through the leg side with the placement to come back for a second
quicker and flatter, played straight to Rashid at deep midwicket
uses his feet and drives sweetly but straight at cover
well bowled, saw Clarke coming and fired it in, flicked to midwicket. Clarke struggling to find the gaps
full toss, punched straight down the ground to long on
backs away and cuts to short third man, there's a fumble which allows them through for a single
nicely bowled again, on middle and a hint of turn, played into the covers and there's some hesitation over the single before they sprint through
dragged down, pulled hard out to deep square-leg

beautiful bowling, tossed up outside off and big spin that beats Ferguson's expansive drive. Sharp work from Prior with the stumping effort, but he had a long way to bring it back and Ferguson's foot is safely in
defended solidly on middle, Rashid has commanded a lot of respect in this spell which is huge credit to a young legspinner
uses his feet and drives through the gap to deep cover
opens the face to find the same gap at cover
outside off, hint of turn, Clarke defends into the off side
touch short and Clarke rocks onto the back foot to drive through the covers
a little quicker this time, defended from the crease back to Swann
flicked off the stumps and can't beat short fine-leg. Tidy stuff from Swann, Australia not getting away here
short and turning away but Clarke can't time it into the covers
oh, that's a wonderful shot, steps down the pitch and goes inside-out over extra cover, once bounce for four. That's the classiest shot of the day so far
goes back and works out to deep square-leg
nearly beaten in the flight as he comes down the pitch and drives, skews off in the air over cover but lands in front of the fielder
punched down to long off, more beat footwork
good finish, flighted on middle, Ferguson defends very watchfully
flighted too much, comes out as a full toss but Clarke can only slam it to cover and he's annoyed at missing out
another deft piece of batting this time, opens the face to a hint of width and guides it past short third man...superb placement
worked from outside off down to long on
tries to chop this to third man, but unlike his captain he is beaten
worked into the leg side, calls for a quick single and that would have been tight if Collingwood had collected cleanly at short midwicket
turned away from straight into the leg side
outside off and pushed firmly through the covers
chopped into the ground and they scamper a single as Prior runs around to do the fielding
driven firmly to mid-on
worked into the leg side, doesn't find the gap
flicked off the stumps down to fine leg, that was pretty straight
driven to midwicket, decent comeback from Anderson
on off stump, tries to place this into the covers but again doesn't beat the fielder
uses his feet and is nearly beaten by some turn from Swann, takes the inside edge to short fine leg
driven down to long off
tucked to square leg
can't beat short fine-leg for the second time in the over...England keeping a tight leash on the innings
full and a hint of inswing for Anderson, driven back to the bowler
backs away outside leg to give himself room, however can only drive to Strauss at cover
good line on off stump, defended with a straight bat towards mid-off but Anderson fields in his follow through
the dot balls are lining up, Ferguson can't get this away from a tight off-stump line
low full toss and again it gets punched back to the bowler, five dots in a row this over
finally gets it away, stepping outside leg again and sends this square through point...looks like a boundary but Wright makes a fine save on the rope
opens the face into the off side
driven firmly through the covers
full ball, tries to find a leg-side gap but goes back to the bowler
tucked to short fine-leg, this time they scamper a single
driven firmly down the pitch, Swann tries to flick it back to the non-strikers' stumps I think but gives away the single
flicked to long on...another regulation over
an inswinger flipped to Rashid at short midwicket who fumbles but eventually gets in a throw.
full toss, bashed through cover! Timed that alright
square driven out to the off side
inswinger which is worked to mid-on
another toss of the full variety, flicked hard through midwicket
chipped out to the off side, and sleepy fielding yields two
faster delivery on middle-and-leg which hurries onto Clarke, or Calekr as I nearly wrote, who nudges to leg
cheeky dance down the pitch; even cheekier bunt to long-off
short of a length and he has plenty of time to work it to leg, but just for a single
flicked to mid-on
worked to the leg side
gets squared up here by a good delivery just outside off, the ball squirting to backward point
nudged off his hip
short of a length and turned to leg
outside off this time and this'll be out! No! Dabbed to backward point where Collingwood lurked, and was perfectly set up to destroy the stumps...but missed them but significant yardage in the end
short of a length, he steps outside leg to try and upset Sidebottom, but it's easily whipped off his hip to leg for another single
guided down to third man
steps outside off this time and tries to work him to leg, but it's a little too short and he's cramped for room. Nevertheless, they steal a run like the daylight robbers they are
very straight and flipped to a wideish mid-on. Very, very slow from Collingwood. He's effectively classed as OB here, not RM
another little cutter, this time worked finer for a single
down the wicket, tries to drive down the ground but is squared up, the ball eventually squeezing low to Shah at cover who dives forward to make a good, tackling catch
a fuller delivery this time to Hussey, who carves him out to the off side
ah, fantastic shot! Ferguson's played this exquisitely, stepping outside leg to give himself room and driving inside out over extra cover. Shot of the day
quick hands gives him a single to leg, whipping it late
cut to Collingwood, who seems to be absolutely everywhere today, who again takes aim and fires at the non-striker's stumps but this time misses
Hussey drops it out to the off side for a quick single
flipped to leg and he gets a single
Hussey flings his bat to get a single to third man, bringing up Australia's 200
tries to flog it over cover but gets a squidy inside edge
on the pull and gets a top-edge but it races down to fine leg for four
short of a length and he works it hard off the back foot to long-on. He works even harder between the wickets, too, grabbing two to bring up a highly impressive fifty from 62. This bloke can play
neat flip off his legs - Anderson has mis-fielded. That's definitely worthy of emboldening, a) so shabby was his fielding and b) so rare is it that he misfields
slower ball patted out to cover
defended on the back foot
shapes back on Hussey who wants a single out to the off side, but Ferguson sends him back and wisely so! Hussey scrambles back into his crease
closeish shout as he's rapped on the pads, but that's probably sliding down
blimey. Miles wide of the off stump as Ferguson inexplicably gave himself a mass of room outside leg. He was probably two metres away from the ball...though Broad's lucky he wasn't wided
an ugly, one-dayish swipe, reaching out for it as though he was trying to reach a floating ball from the banks of a river
that's right in the slot and slotted for four, carving him square and timing it brilliantly. Serious power!
reaches out for it but can't, well, reach it. Drives and misses and looks back at the umpire with a puppy-dog "come on, ump. Surely that's a wide?" expression
guided to Sidebottom at short third man
down the pitch to a full toss, a high one too, and slaps it down to third man for four!
cramped for room and tries to pull
reverse sweep for four! That's possibly the most deft stroke we've seen all day - real class and awareness by Ferguson. Absolutely super shot!
leading edge out to cover but they're all pretty deep out there, and it falls safe
down the leg side and tries to turn it around the corner but misses
flipped through square leg, and in fact he's placed that nicely for three

another great shot which Broad pulls back quite superbly with a dive at long-off. Broad could've really hurt himself there. Terrific shot again from Ferguson, bisecting cover and mid-off - and in fact that's been given four after a couple of replays.
wow - this is a bit special. A paddle-sweep - he got onto that so quickly, scooping it fine for four.
what a comeback that is! Quicker, much fuller and straighter. Hussey tried to open the face and guide him out square, but lost his middle stump

guided out on the back foot. Oh dear. That's rubbish from England. Three players converge on the ball, and neither of them want to field it, allowing them two when even a single would've been too many!
cracked out to cover
bowled! Very, very full and angling into Ferguson who stepped to leg and was in no-man's land in the end. Tried a meek defensive push, but the length was too full

full toss flipped to mid-on - they're going for two, and Hopes really will have to hurry here. He puts in a dive and somehow head-butts the ground in doing so, almost somersaulting over the line! Good commitment
driven to long-on and they come back for two. He'll have to be quick! in comes the throw and he whips off the bails, and that is mighty, mighty close, but ruled not-out by the third umpire
driven out to mid-off
squeezed out down to third man
full toss, smacked to third man
down the pitch, charging Broad, and slapping him to cover
smacked to long-off
smashed back down the ground and it destroys the stumps, but Sidebottom didn't get a finger on it
another full toss, again banged down the ground and they'll have to really scurry if they're to get two...but they do! Great effort
and another full toss! This time bashed out to cover, and not quite timed
excellent take by Prior down the leg side, as Sidebottom fires in an attempted yorker which slides down leg
a full toss given the treatment, or nearly, over midwicket - not quite perfectly timed but sufficiently placed for four. Good, solid blow
slashed to third man

inn2.comm: good line outside off, Strauss shoulders arms and it carries through at ankle height to Tim Paine
left alone again outside off
well bowled, extra bounce on that one as Lee drags his length back a bit, Strauss drops his hands and pulls the bat inside the line
another leave, as Lee probes outside off, good speeds at 93mph...will be interesting to see what role Strauss plays. An aggressor or an anchor.
goes for the drive, gets a thick inside half of the bat through square leg and there's a brace to launch England's innings as long leg comes round
beaten to end the over, he certainly played at that one and there are smiles from Strauss and Lee. A good contest in the offing
good line to Bopara first up, on off stump and defended softly into the covers
on leg stump and nicely flicked away by Bopara, very fine and long leg is far to square to get anywhere near that...short boundary that direction at The Oval
back on off stump, Bopara pushes back down the pitch
on middle, turned into the leg side
angling across the right hander, no sign of any swing yet, left alone to the keeper
defends tightly to his body, watching the ball onto the bat and playing to backward point
wide outside off, carries one bounce through to Paine
this time Strauss brings out the cut, slices down to third man and it's a no-ball as well
well bowled, opts for the slower-ball bouncer and Bopara doesn't make contact...the batsman will be annoyed at that
neatly punched up to mid-on, good position from Bopara
ooh, nearly gets a leading edge as he tries to turn into the leg side
loses his line with a slower ball, goes down the leg side and that's another extra
tucked into the leg side, may have been tight if the fielder had collected but it's another no-ball
backs away to the leg side, Lee responds by firing it well outside off and it's called a wide...so the free hit carries over to the next ball
that's more like it...crunched down the ground, backed away again and swung hard through the line sending it straight past the stumps with plenty of power
finally the over ends, on off stump and defended to mid-off
flicked away from leg stump with a turn of the wrists but picks out the man at short fine-leg
rides some extra bounce nicely, worked out to deeps square-leg
worked away through square leg in typically compact style
plays a walking defensive shot, as is his style, up to mid off
slower ball, picked by Bopara who defends with bat and pad together
solid defence into the covers, nothing too flashy yet from Bopara
full outside off, Strauss doesn't get any power or timing onto his drive into the covers
ooh, lucky for Strauss, goes for a pull to a ball that wasn't quite short enough and gets a bottom edge that flies past the stumps and down to fine leg

gone! there's the breakthrough for Australia, Strauss flashes hard outside off and sends a comfortable catch to Cameron White at slip, who bounces it in front of his face. The width was on offer for Strauss and the cut is a strong shot
that's rapid, a ripping bouncer from Lee that Prior fends off from in front of his grill and it flies in the direction of where short leg would have been...that's tasty
follows up with full ball on off stump that Prior drives wide of mid-off to open his account
good line outside off, left alone to end an impressive over
dropped square into the off side, they set off for a quick single as Clarke fields and Nathan Bracken does a brilliant job backing up because that could have been four overthrows
comes forward, takes the outside edge wide and short of slip...once it beats the man it races to the short third-man boundary

is he going to be run out? No...steps across his stumps and turns into the leg side, then there is confusion as Bopara wants two but is sent back. A good throw from Watson would have had him in trouble as he dives for his ground
some width for Prior who loves it there, flayed through the off side and Lee runs round from third man...his throw almost evades everyone, but the backing up is good again
worked nicely off his pads down to long leg
tucked away to deep square leg again, Bracken's line just a little too straight
comes forward and pushes square into the off side, 91mph from Lee who is cranking up the speed
hops back into the crease and defends very correctly back towards Lee
back of a length, Bopara jumps into line and works it from his hip down to long leg...that was 93mph, serious speed
clever, clever bowling, a slower ball from Lee and Prior almost plays too early as he forces off the back foot
confident pull, in the air for quite a while but lands well short of Bracken at long leg
unconvincing that time from Bopara, he's fishing outside off...or he may actually have been trying to pull out of the shot...but either way the ball runs off the face wide of the slips to third man
flicked in the air through midwicket, 90mph, but it seemed to stop in the pitch and Bopara was caught playing early
pushed back to Johnson in his follow through
forced off the back foot into the covers, 93mph that time
uses his wrists again to take the ball from a fairly straight line down to long leg
plays at the top of the bounce, defended to square cover
stays back in his crease to a full ball and drives to mid-off, but his weight wasn't really coming into the shot
on off stump, defended into the covers
chopped away square on the off side, was probably enough width to put that one away
chopped into the ground by the stumps, bobbles towards backward point
good line, forces Bopara to defend to cover when he would like to attacking in the Powerplay
Nips back off the seam, cramps Bopara for room as he defends
goes for the cut, doesn't time it and bottom edges down the pitch...a maiden to start with, excellent start for Hopes
good line, defended into the covers
lovely cover drive, hammered through the covers in fine styke, was a touch full and he leaned into the shot
fired wide outside off, Prior reaches for it but can't make contact...Johnson gets away with the wide call
dropped short, latches on a pull but Ferguson at deep square makes an excellent save to prevent the boundary
slower ball outside off, Prior tries to angle it away but doesn't make contact...Johnson using his variations
defended square to end the over
nice off-drive but lacking power
and cash in he does! Outrageous class from Bopara cover-driving with authority, placement and timing. Good grief that was a good-looking shot
an elegant flick to leg brings up England's fifty
touch of swing back into Prior who defends solidly off the back foot
slower ball just outside off but he reads it well and pats it out to mid-off
he got better hold of that, driving firmly to mid-off
beaten outside off! Lovely delivery
just outside off and guided to point
beaten once more, this is superb bowling by Johnson. Angled across Bopara and it holds its own, beating Bopara who played at it expecting it to cut back on him. Really good length again from Johnson
nudged to leg
slower ball and well bowled
and rightly so. That was a little too wide of the off stump

fast, fast, fast and that beats Prior's flash outside off, and beats young Paine too - and could easily have smashed into his face. He got down low but it was onto him so quickly, flashing through his gloves and he snapped his head out of the way
driven firmly on the up
stands tall and drives off the back foot to mid-on
driven out to the off side - White has to swivel on it at short-extra but eventually lets go of it, and it's a decent throw but he wasn't quite quick enough to release
pushed off the back foot
neatly guided out to point
slower delivery and tucked around the corner
that's just short of a length. Back goes Bopara, defending it out to the off side
good, straight delivery and he's back into a defensive
poor old bowlers. They've not got a hope in ODIs, really. Half a foot outside leg and it's wided
91mph full toss just outside the off stump and pumped to point
bouncer which he ducks beneath. No great pace
solid defensive on the front foot - they want a single and they just get it
played with soft hands down to third man
a flourishing, good-looking square cut finds backward point
excellent stop by Bracken and his Alice band at short fine leg
an indeterminate defensive on the back foot. Bat coming down at a diagonal angle, and he gets a thick inside edge onto his pads
a flashing cut and he misses
a swift single, flicking to leg
glitzily cut to third man
top-edged into his face! Never really got down enough to sweep it properly; it was a horrid KPish flick, and he deservedly got smashed in the grill for it
cut out through the covers
ignored outside off and wided
even wider still but Bopara reaches for it and drives, opening the face down to third man. Touch and class from Bopara there, though that really was horrendously wide
off the back foot this time, pumped to long-on
tossed up very wide and Prior shovels it off the back foot out to the off side. A raking sort of stroke, as though clearing leaves from the driveway with a long-handled rake. Anyway
better line - best ball of the over. Just outside off and he works it to leg defensively
outside off, Prior defends with a dab behind square and Bopara demands Prior gets the heck back in his crease after briefly considering a mad run
that's a very good length. Prior should've been on the front foot there, and had to play it very late on the back foot instead
a little leg cutter which he dabs to fine leg
good line and length, defended out to the off side
crunched to cover
a solid defensive for a single to mid-off
stroked to long-off for a single
defended on the back foot to mid-on
hurries onto Prior who can only defend
swept/paddled to shortish fine leg
another single. Good play by England, this
another premeditated sweep around the corner
cuts and misses. Good, quicker ball from Hauritz
tossed up wider and thrashed out to mid-off
cut hard out to deep cover point
flighted wider and beats him! Drifted a touch away from Bopara who was lured into it. Remarkably not called a wide, though...
straighter and nudged to leg
tossed up and turned to leg
flicked around the corner
slides down the leg side; great take by Paine
defended on the back foot
Prior cuts this hard - for four!
paddled around the corner

that's gone! Prior goes for the reverse sweep and is well caught a short third man...that was a pretty needless shot in the circumstances, with these two having set a platform, and Prior hangs his head before walking off
width outside off, flayed through the covers by Shah to get off the mark
wide outside off again, out to the cover sweeper
worked from outside off down the on side, Hauritz skips across to field
cut away into the off side, they decline a single but then Johnson's fierce throw is too much for Hauritz and they get an overthrow
played into the off side
opens the face and finds the gap at cover
driven square, opens the face to try and find the gap but can't pierce the field
pushed easily into the off side
goes down for a lap-sweep, gets the ball at 45 on the leg side
collects another single out to deep cover, good rotation of the strike
swept down to deep backward square, fairly comfortable over from Clarke
dropped into the off side, they think of a single but decline...these two aren't the best between the wickets
worked into the leg side
good use of the wrists but can't find the gap at midwicket
lovely drive from Bopara, slightly inside-out all along the ground through cover and wide enough of long off for a second
straighter from Hauritz, played into the leg side
beats cover with good placement again, two more for Bopara but Hauritz is doing a good job
down the pitch from Shah, he clubs that over a wide mid-on area and it falls well short of the deep fielder...they only manage a single, but some intent from Shah
worked to the leg side
tucked out to deep sqaure
opens the face to backward point
chopped away off the stumps, skidded through from Clarke but it's well placed wide of point
swept from middle and off, gets it down through short fine leg and keeps the strike
stays in his crease, waits for it and picks the gap to deep square
punched neatly down to long on...brings up England's 100 to a ripple of applause
wild drive outside off, Paine whips the bails off for a stumping but Bopara's back foot gets back in time
skips down the pitch outside off and drives down to long on
opens the face and finds short third man
helped down the ground again, England ticking over at the moment
great response from Shah first up, a wide full delivery and it's drilled through the covers with enough power to beat the sweeper...top batting
slammed off the back foot to mid off who is inside the circle
dragged down short, a slower-ball bouncer and Shah waits for it well, just manages to hold back the shot long enough and helps it out to deep square for another boundary
punched off the back foot to cover
back of a length outside off, Shah well back towards his stumps as he pushes out to cover
solid defence to end the over, punches straight down the ground
tossed up outside off, driven easily through the covers
very wide outside, and too wide this time
dropped into the off side and a well taken quick single as Paine scampers to do the fielding
very full, almost a yorker, and dug into the leg side
pushed firmly to cover
turned off middle to short fine leg where Lee prevents the single
down the track and heaved to long on...another tight over from Hauritz
round the wicket, pushed down the ground to long off
opens the face and picks out backward point
width outside off allows Shah to free his arms, slashing the ball away wide of third man so he can come back for a second
well bowled, a slower-ball yorker from round the wicket, Shah does well to dig it out
driven firmly down to long off
angled away from outside off, picks out the Australia captain at backward point
gee, Shah gets this so fine past the keeper - it almost classes as a catch - and it races down to third man
fired down the leg side
driven square through covers, Shah brings out his full follow through the bat

Hauritz gets the breakthrough...a nice piece of bowling as he flights the ball past the outside edge and Bopara drags his foot outside the crease. Bopara knows he's out as Paine whips off the bails and is almost off the ground by the time the third umpire confirms the decision

what is going on there! That was almost shambolic from England as Collingwood drops the ball past slip and wants the single, Shah comes then stops then sets off again. Eventually both players get back, but Collingwood isn't impressed

almost another run out as Collingwood is beaten by one that rips through the gate, he bounces off Paine to short fine leg and Collingwood is late setting off the single but makes his ground as the throw is wide
beaten outside off to end a fine, maybe match-changing, over
stays round the wicket, played to backward point
defended solidly out to cover...England need to take a few deep breathes here and compose themselves
driven off a thick inside edge to midwicket
punched back to the bowler, but the ball is making a very clunky sound which doesn't suggest much timing from Collingwood
back to Bracken again who makes a good save in his follow through
pushed down the ground to long off as he gets off the mark
super sweep, played it really fine. Very fine indeed
tossed up much slower this time. Patted out to the off side
slapped powerfully through cover but Ferguson does well to haul it back in
a crunching hit by Shah back to Hauritz who did well to react as quickly as he did
nice bowling, much faster. Shah drills it to long-on
another sweep and well executed, but not quite as fine as his first one
forced to point
short of a length and turned to midwicket
ooh, well bowled. Nice and full and he went for a crashing cover drive but got a thick inside edge
plenty of bottom hand in that. Bashed to mid-off
defended on the back foot
driven elegantly to long-off
nudged to long-on
pushed back to the bowler
a wide down the leg side
stroked out nicely to extra cover
good shot. Crunched to long-off powerfully
down the pitch and chips it to midwicket
solid bunt to long-on
driven out to extra cover
very full - that's the length - and well hit out to the off side
ooh that's close! That's hit him in front of the off stump as he attempted a sweep, but no, it's outside the line
crunched out to the off side. I say crunched - driven without any power off the back foot, with one hand coming off the bat
onto the front foot and drives out to the off side
driven square of the wicket
Collingwood drives through the line to one just outside his off stump. Long-off cleans up
nice and straight. Good start from Watson. Shah's defending on the back foot with the straightest of bats
comes forward before dabbing it to third man
cut out to the off side
a massive swing and a miss from Shah! Horrible-looking flapping swipe
touch of inswing to him but he drives for a single out to long-off
spears into the batsman who drives out to the off side
driven just short of Nathan Bracken and his Alice band. Nearly!
nice idea, going for a paddly sweep, but short fine-leg is there

driven back to Bracken who misfields it through his legs, allowing them a single. And - wayhay! - Watson slips on the now-greasy grass and ends up looking a little silly. Probably gets the biggest cheer of the day
slower ball! Beautifully bowled. 65mph and Shah dobs it out to the off side a bit cluelessly
opens the face to short third man
full toss, banged to Clarke at point. Clarke's now smiling ... I think they just sense England haven't got what it takes to up the rate here
neat nudge for a single. But just a single
very straight. This is excellent from Watson. Another just-a-single single to the leg side
bashed out to cover
tries to whack it over midwicket but cludgily finds wide mid-on. No timing
flicked to leg and they get two whole runs. First signs of urgency, of aggression?
punched out to long-off
swivels onto a pull and very well he's timed it, too. Touch too straight and he really placed it well, too

a nurdle off his pads for a single. Or two? Er, no, he's out - he's not just stepped on the stumps, he's trampled on them as though his leg stump was Joe Denly's left knee. Gone! What a calamitous way for him to depart
flashes and misses, but at least he didn't stamp on his stumps like our Owais
off the mark with a push out past point
blocked off the back foot
a full toss given some bottom-handed bunt to long-off
Collingwood defends solidly on the front foot. That's the way
very full and swings in late, he tries to drive down the ground but can't time it
strong shot, but his cut finds third man
poked out to point and they take a quick single. The fielder fumbles
a thick, Collingwoody inside edge for a strike-stealing single
short of a length and cut hard out to the off side
nudged to leg
driven out to the off side - excellent dive by mid-off! White is the man, in every sense conceivable
patted out to the off side, but they can't get a single, and The Oval crowd roundly boo them. Bit harsh, frankly

excellent catch by Watson, really excellent! Collingwood goes on the pull to one outside the off stump, but he mistimes it. Watson had to make a big leap but he, on the other hand, timed it perfectly to pluck it out of the air! Great stuff
defended to mid-on
well, well, Wright goes for it and launches Watson straight down the ground for the first six of the day and what a time to do it...a clean strike straight through the line over and over long off
pushed out to backward point
drifting into the pads, goes into the leg side and Broad is nearly run out as he came charging up the pitch...a direct hit would have had him
another strong drive, along the ground on this occasion and straight to long off
beaten as he drives off the back foot
driven hard square of the wicket but it's just a single to the sweeper
carved away down to third man...England need to find the boundary every over really
short outside off, cut hard through the covers but straight at the sweeper
another one goes, banged in on off stump, Broad tries to upper-cut it over point but instead just lobs a catch to Clarke inside the circle and Australia are scenting the win here
clubbed into the covers and these two should be quick between the wickets
beaten outside off as he pushes without any footwork, the ball bounces in front of Paine who makes a good stop
full outside off and guided firmly to backward point where Clarke is in the action again
well, Wright's going for it, he backs away to leg and Lee follows him, Wright swings hard with a pull-turned-hoick and somehow finds mid off
connects well this time, a powerful pull ("almost a tennis swat," says Will) and it beats deep square to the boundary
another boundary, fortunate this time as Wright almost swings himself off his feet and gets an inside edge past the keeper
responds with a yorker, Wright digs it out towards cover who is on the edge of the circle and there's a single on offer
low full toss at the stumps, took Rashid by surprise and he just pats it back down the pitch to Lee
an ugly heave from Rashid, moves to the leg side and swats it over cover...the ball loops over Ferguson at mid-off but he manages to pull it up short of the rope
opens the face to point, they race off for a single and Rashid makes it
round the wicket, angling into the pads and Rashid can't make contact as he tries a sweep
good shot from Rashid, moves his left leg so he can drive through the covers but Watson makes a superb save on the cover boundary
another handsome strike from Wright, he gets under the ball and launches it over mid-on...lands just short of the rope, this is Wright's role
slower ball, driven into the covers
he finds the boundary this time, gave himself a touch of room and flayed the ball through the covers...Rashid has plenty of talent with the bat and he's in form
a slower-ball short ball again, Wright is early on the shot and takes a blow on the shoulder...wants a single, but is sent back and is almost run out by Lee's direct hit
backs away and slices this away over backward point, third man comes around and cuts it off...the atmosphere has certainly lifted
well bowled from Lee, saw Wright trying to make room and fired in a leg-stump yorker which is squeezed out into the covers
a full-pace bouncer, Rashid doesn't make contact as he swings across the line
excellent stuff from Lee, full and very fast at Rashid's feet...the batsman gets into a tangle playing it, but they somehow scamper a single as Lee fields and hurls the ball past the stumps
another yorker dug out into the leg side, top over from Lee
full outside off, Wright misses his swing but Paine can't collect cleanly...it was an awkward bounce so he actually did well to save four
wild and wide outside, the bounced beyond the end of the cut strip...Watson didn't look happy at any stage before, during or after that ball
well bowled, almost the perfect yorker, dug out to backward point
brilliant, inventive, brave shot from Wright...goes down on one knee and paddles Watson over short fine leg for another boundary
swings hard outside off, doesn't make contact but it's too wide again and the pressure starting to show on Watson
tries to paddle past short fine-leg again, doesn't beat him this time
slower ball outside off, not too wide this time and a precious dot for Australia
and third man nearly has a catch as Rashid gets a thick top edge to a huge swing, but the ball lands short of the man
backs away, chopped to backward point and a misfield from White allows them back for a second...the ball just got away from him as he dived
brilliant yorker, dug out straight down the pitch and they manage a single virtually to the bowler...very alert from Wright and Rashid
low full toss outside leg, Wright had backed away again and pings it straight to mid on
another pinpoint yorker, Rashid can only drive it to mid off

it all happened there! Run out off a no-ball! Wright moved across his stumps to try and flick it through short fine leg, misses the ball and sets off for a bye. Paine hits with his throw and Wright is well out...Wright checks if he is out, the umpire confirms the news. You can be run out off a no-ball, but not stumped
a bouncer on the free fit, Swann can't make contact with his pull, well bowled
backs away outside leg and angles the ball to third man
swung away through the leg side, they make it back for two
full ball heaved into the on side, can't beat the field
banged in short, Rashid swings hard but just clobbers it into the ground and it bobbles towards the wicketkeeper

another goes and Australia close in, a slower ball from Watson and Swann gets a thick outside edge as he swings hard. A regulation catch for Paine who has had an excellent day with the gloves after his earlier run out for a duck
works his ball into the leg side as Sidebottom gets away first ball
chopped away through short third man, Bracken chases hard but can't pull it in
well, well, Sidebottom gets a top edge over the keeper as he swings hard at a short ball from Lee
another edge past the keeper! Sidebottom pushes at a full toss and it flies past Paine down to third man
edged again down to third man but straight to the fielder this time, but England will want Rashid to have the strike
swings hard and the ball flies past leg stump...valuable dot for Australia
what a shot, what a shot from Rashid, leans back and hammers Rashid through the covers for a cracking boundary...one of the shots of the day and England aren't giving this up
swung down to long, Rashid will keep the strike for the last over
swing and a miss outside off

another fine blow from Rashid, a big full toss from Bracken and it's swung away powerfully out through deep square-leg...some controversy over the height, it did look pretty close to a no-ball, but it's ruled okay by the umpires
chopped away to short third man, just a single and it's over to Sidebottom

oh dear, oh dear, Sidebottom leaves the ball thinking it was a wide but he doesn't get the call from Tony Hill...that almost seals the game unless he can now find the boundary. He should have at least thrown the bat at it
swung hard into the covers, at least he hit this one, and they come back for a couple
he fires in a yorker and Sidebottom can only squeeze it down to long off...Bracken holds his nerve and Australia win by four runs
